  {
    "slug": "vamosavenezuela",
    "name": "VamosaVenezuela",
    "one_liner": "A booking platform for the Venezuela you haven't seen — curated stays, dining, and experiences across every region of the country.",
    "status": "Active",
    "client": "VCP build",
    "website": "https://vamosavenezuela.com/",
    "logo": "assets/logos/vamosavenezuela.svg",
    "overview": "<p>VamosaVenezuela is a travel guide and trip-planning platform for Venezuelan tourism. It curates places to stay, dining, and activities across eight regions — Los Roques, Mérida and the Andes, Canaima and Angel Falls, Morrocoy, Margarita, Gran Sabana, Caracas, Barquisimeto — plus landscape categories from beaches and islands to tepuis and jungle.</p><p>Beyond destination guides, the platform ships real planning tools: an interactive map, flight search, sample trips, and a custom itinerary builder. Every destination carries an editorial safety rating, so travelers know what to expect before they commit.</p>",
    "timeline": null,
    "moat": "<p>Editorial curation plus a per-destination safety-rating system — a trust layer no generic travel site offers for Venezuela. The content depth across all eight regions, hidden gems included, is the kind of ground-truth coverage a competitor can't scrape together quickly.</p>",
    "business_model": "<p>Audience-first: the platform builds traffic through curated destination content, with flight search and stay/experience listings as the natural referral and booking surfaces to monetize as the audience grows.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: var(--space-5);\">Five-year revenue forecast <span class=\"placeholder-note\">[draft — Jose refines]</span></h3><p>Monthly platform profit on total booking revenue handled through VamosaVenezuela, at a projected average 10% commission — 10% of that profit is pledged to Venezuelan non-profits through the platform's donation channel. The curve is a logistic adoption ramp with Venezuelan tourism seasonality — December–January, Easter, and August peaks. Hover any month for the underlying booking volume and the non-profit split; every figure is an illustrative planning target.</p><figure style=\"margin: var(--space-4) 0 0;\" aria-label=\"Line chart: monthly platform profit rising from roughly $286 in month one to $15k by month sixty, with seasonal peaks each December and August.\"><svg viewBox=\"0 0 720 340\" width=\"100%\" role=\"img\" aria-hidden=\"false\" style=\"display:block; max-width:100%;\"><line x1=\"64\" y1=\"300.0\" x2=\"696\" y2=\"300.0\" stroke=\"var(--line)\"/><text x=\"56\" y=\"303.5\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-family=\"var(--font-mono)\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"var(--text-faint)\">$0</text><line x1=\"64\" y1=\"246.0\" x2=\"696\" y2=\"246.0\" stroke=\"var(--line)\"/><text x=\"56\" y=\"249.5\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-family=\"var(--font-mono)\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"var(--text-faint)\">$3k</text><line x1=\"64\" y1=\"192.0\" x2=\"696\" y2=\"192.0\" stroke=\"var(--line)\"/><text x=\"56\" y=\"195.5\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-family=\"var(--font-mono)\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"var(--text-faint)\">$6k</text><line x1=\"64\" y1=\"138.0\" x2=\"696\" y2=\"138.0\" stroke=\"var(--line)\"/><text x=\"56\" y=\"141.5\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-family=\"var(--font-mono)\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"var(--text-faint)\">$9k</text><line x1=\"64\" y1=\"84.0\" x2=\"696\" y2=\"84.0\" stroke=\"var(--line)\"/><text x=\"56\" y=\"87.5\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-family=\"var(--font-mono)\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"var(--text-faint)\">$12k</text><line x1=\"64\" y1=\"30.0\" x2=\"696\" y2=\"30.0\" stroke=\"var(--line)\"/><text x=\"56\" y=\"33.5\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-family=\"var(--font-mono)\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"var(--text-faint)\">$15k</text><text x=\"122.9\" y=\"326\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-family=\"var(--font-mono)\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"var(--text-faint)\">YEAR 1</text><text x=\"251.5\" y=\"326\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-family=\"var(--font-mono)\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"var(--text-faint)\">YEAR 2</text><text x=\"380.0\" y=\"326\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-family=\"var(--font-mono)\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"var(--text-faint)\">YEAR 3</text><text x=\"508.5\" y=\"326\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-family=\"var(--font-mono)\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"var(--text-faint)\">YEAR 4</text><text x=\"637.1\" y=\"326\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-family=\"var(--font-mono)\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"var(--text-faint)\">YEAR 5</text><line x1=\"192.5\" y1=\"30\" x2=\"192.5\" y2=\"300\" stroke=\"var(--line)\" stroke-dasharray=\"2 4\"/><line x1=\"321.1\" y1=\"30\" x2=\"321.1\" y2=\"300\" stroke=\"var(--line)\" stroke-dasharray=\"2 4\"/><line x1=\"449.6\" y1=\"30\" x2=\"449.6\" y2=\"300\" stroke=\"var(--line)\" stroke-dasharray=\"2 4\"/><line x1=\"578.2\" y1=\"30\" x2=\"578.2\" y2=\"300\" stroke=\"var(--line)\" stroke-dasharray=\"2 4\"/><path d=\"M64.0,294.8 L74.7,295.9 L85.4,295.1 L96.1,293.7 L106.8,294.6 L117.6,293.7 L128.3,291.8 L139.0,288.7 L149.7,292.3 L160.4,290.9 L171.1,288.1 L181.8,280.9 L192.5,281.7 L203.3,285.4 L214.0,283.0 L224.7,278.3 L235.4,281.5 L246.1,278.4 L256.8,272.2 L267.5,262.2 L278.2,274.5 L288.9,270.3 L299.7,261.8 L310.4,239.5 L321.1,243.1 L331.8,255.5 L342.5,249.0 L353.2,236.1 L363.9,246.7 L374.6,239.3 L385.4,223.9 L396.1,199.2 L406.8,233.8 L417.5,225.1 L428.2,20